HOUSE BILL No. 1048
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 36-8-12-5.
Synopsis: VFD clothing and automobile allowances. Increases, from
$100 to $250, the clothing and automobile allowance for an active
member of a volunteer fire department.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Novak
December 5, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Veterans Affairs and
Public Safety.
2026 IN 1048—LS 6378/DI 116

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1048
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning local
government.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 36-8-12-5 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
2 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) Unless otherwise
3 provided by contract, a unit served by a volunteer fire department shall
4 pay to each active and participating member of the department:
5 (1) a clothing allowance of not less than one hundred dollars
6 ($100) two hundred fifty dollars ($250) per year; and
7 (2) an automobile allowance of not less than one hundred dollars
8 ($100) two hundred fifty dollars ($250) per year for the use of
9 the member's automobile in the line of duty.
10 (b) A contract may also provide that fees for membership in a
11 regularly organized volunteer firefighters' association be paid by the
12 unit on behalf of the firefighters in the volunteer fire department.
